21:19.800 --> 21:25.440
international students in engineering oh

21:25.420 --> 21:34.740
we started getting them way back there in the 60s 
some and i would not i was trying to at one time we had

21:34.720 --> 21:41.180
some pressure on us to not have more than 30 percent 
in engineering graduate students and i kept mine

21:41.160 --> 21:48.460
down and uh i tried to keep them down we could have 
had a bigger class of graduate students and one of

21:48.440 --> 21:53.840
the things that we did to try to attract others 
would take these that had finished with a

21:53.820 --> 22:00.660
four-year degree in science from some of these 
teaching colleges and get them in give them a a fast

22:00.640 --> 22:04.780
course but that's when it started and now there's 
just probably no uh no holds barred you can have any

22:04.780 --> 22:12.800
number you want to there was some concern that the 
legislature would be concerned about us

22:12.780 --> 22:17.380
educating so many foreign students and that 
prevailed uh a long time through engineering over

22:17.360 --> 22:25.340
there and we did keep ours down what would you be 
your evaluation of the quality of the

22:25.320 --> 22:30.900
international students the academic ability oh i 
think they're good uh but i another thing that i

22:34.800 --> 22:42.730
think is uh that they are going to be the leaders 
unless we uh i think that we might want to give some

22:42.710 --> 22:49.730
favoritism to ours and because what's happening 
to our own students now is that they can get a good

22:49.710 --> 22:55.430
salary when they get the bs degree so they're going 
out and taking that job and i'm not so sure but what

22:55.410 --> 23:02.720
there's nothing wrong with being showing 
favoritism over your own national students so

